cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with human action recognition from skeleton data. The use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) with LSTM architecture suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The proposed view adaptation scheme involves adapting to the most suitable observation viewpoints, which suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of skeleton data suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of RNNs suggests that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
